<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="376" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="19.[140,1108,166,369]" pageId="19" pageNumber="376">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Horn" baseAuthorityYear="1880" box="[185,342,237,263]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Leiodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="376" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="valida">
<emphasis box="[185,342,237,263]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="376">Leiodes valida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is newly recorded in Labrador, Newfoundland, and 
<collectingRegion box="[960,1104,237,263]" country="Canada" name="Nova Scotia" pageId="19" pageNumber="376">Nova Scotia</collectingRegion>
. It was recorded from 
<collectingRegion box="[392,576,272,299]" country="Canada" name="New Brunswick" pageId="19" pageNumber="376">New Brunswick</collectingRegion>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Baranowski" box="[623,841,272,298]" firstAuthor="Baranowski" pageId="19" pageNumber="376" pagination="1 - 149" refId="ref22548" refString="Baranowski R (1993) Revision of the genus Leiodes Latreille of North and Central America (Coleoptera: Leiodidae). Entomological Scandinavia Supplement 42: 1 - 149." type="journal article" year="1993">Baranowski (1993)</bibRefCitation>
(
<figureCitation box="[859,931,272,298]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="15.[140,174,1622,1644]" captionTargetBox="[140,1109,872,1603]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[141,1109,873,1602]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig. 4. Distribution of Leiodes assimilis, Leiodes collaris, Leiodes punctostriata. Leiodes strigata, and Leiodes valida in the Atlantic Provinces. Some locations in Labrador are not shown." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3770890" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3770890/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="376">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). It is the largest North American species in the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1796" box="[611,689,307,333]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Leiodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="376" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[611,689,307,333]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="376">Leiodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Nothing is known of its bionomics (
<bibRefCitation author="Baranowski" box="[147,350,342,369]" firstAuthor="Baranowski" pageId="19" pageNumber="376" pagination="1 - 149" refId="ref22548" refString="Baranowski R (1993) Revision of the genus Leiodes Latreille of North and Central America (Coleoptera: Leiodidae). Entomological Scandinavia Supplement 42: 1 - 149." type="journal article" year="1993">Baranowski 1993</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
